review_blob: Aroma of mild malt. Pale yellow color. Starts off sort of sweetish, finishes sort of skunky. Yep thats it.

I love bourbon ales, and pumpkins. I figured this would be amazing. It wasnt. It has a amber color. Has slight pumpkin aroma. Flavor starts off a bit sweet, than has harsh bourbon, and a bad canned pumpkin flavor. It has a rough finish. Just not great.

Aroma of pumpkin, spice, caramel, malt, and cinnamon. Color is deep orange hue. Nice complex flavor of pumpkin, cinnamon, allspice, pepper, oak, caramel, malt, and burnt wood. Has a clean but spicy finish. great choice!
beer_name: Tyranena Painted Ladies Pumpkin Spice Ale

review_blob: Light pumpkin smell. light overall color. Really just a bland ale. No pumpkin flavor or any type of spice. Not sure if I got a bad bottle.

Fantastic fresh pumpkin aroma. Rich dark amber hue. It has a rich, creamy, slightly sweet overall taste. You get a ripe pumpkin flavor, with all the pumpkin pie spices, mixed in with a hearty nutty flavor. Clean finish Excellent oktoberfest beer!
Aroma is pumpkin and nutmeg. Rich orange color. It has a strong nutmeg, and allspice taste. Not much else.

beer_brewer_name: The Traveler Beer Company (formerly House Of Shandy)
review_blob: Aroma is of pumkin pie. It has a light appearance. It has a very light mouthful. Overall the taste is pumpkin and allspice. Light beer but not bad.
Slight aroma of bread. Rich amber color. Sweet, malt, bread, with a clean finish. Not bad but not the best oktoberfest.

Dark brown color. Has a pleasant mild aroma. Wonderful combination of pecans, walnuts, caramel, vanilla, butter, malt, and oak char.It has a hint of sweetness but its not over powering. Finishes clean and smooth. This was a wonderful beer, easy to drink but full of flavor.
Smells like fruits and nuts. Has a dark ruby color. Has a taste of cherries, figs, plums, mixed with a port wine. Later you get a taste of oak, combined with some hops. It has a bitter finish.

Its a great beer! It pours a rich red color. It smells like fresh berries. It blends in sugar, raspberries, some nuts, touch of cream, and finishes clean. Its not too sweet, and its great. For my own tastes if they could make it a bit more tart like a framboise I might have to give 5 stars.

Nearly perfect. It tastes like a chocolate covered orange peel. If they could bring out the chocolate a bit more it would be perfect. It has a pure black color. It smells of chocolate and oranges. It combined sugar, chocolate, orange, cream, and oak to make a complex beer. It has a slightly bitter finish like a chocolate covered orange peel.
beer_name: Southern Tier Blackwater Series: Choklat Oranj

review_blob: Another one of my favorite beers. Its basically the best possible stout, combined with creme brulee whats not to love. It pours a deep black. It smells of fresh vanilla. It blends together cream, chocolate, sugar, oak, toffee, nuts, and malt in the perfect mix. Its a bit sweet but its supposed to be. Just amazing.
beer_name: Southern Tier Blackwater Series: Creme Brulee Stout

review_blob: It has a beautiful rich amber hue. It smells like a fresh pumpkin pie. It blends in a combination of pumpkin, nuts, cinnamon, sugar, nutmeg, and cream together in a wonderful combination. It feels like drinking a delicious pumpkin pie.
I was expecting it to be a lot better. Pale orange color. Nice biscuits baking aroma. Has a very light mouthful, and very watery. Slightly sweet, with a slight malty taste. Just a bit disappointing.
It has a pleasant nutty aroma. Pours a deep brown color. It has a nice mix of nuts, caramel, malt, and a touch of hops. Its solid but not anything special.

Has a great aroma of bread and caramel. Pours a nice rich black color. Has a really nice blend of smoky, doughy, caramel, malt, with a touch of sweet fruit. The only negative of this beer, is its a little thin. A little more alcohol, and a bit thicker and this would be a 4+. It has such a nice flavor I wish they would crank it up a bit.
Its just bitter. really bitter. really super over the top, killing all other flavor bitter. It has a pleasant aroma, which would be great if I can get this bitter flavor off my tongue.
beer_name: Horny Goat Hopped Up N Horny IPA

review_blob: Light color. Slight ginger aroma. lightly sweet with a hint of ginger. Not a very complex beer. Glad I tried it, but probably not going to try it again.

Rich amber color. Has a nice aroma of sweet citrus fruit, and pine. The flavor is a wonderful mix of tangy IPA, sweet citrus, sweet malty caramel, tart fruit, and spicy rye. It has a fantastic balance and is a great beer.
beer_name: Great Lakes Rye of the Tiger

review_blob: Pours a black thick head. Has a nice rich choclate, roasted coffe aroma. Has a taste of sweet bread, chocolate, malt, smoke, and coffee. Is a little bitter finish. Overall a solid choice.

Yes Please!

Has a sweet citrus y nose. Has a nice golden color that is beautiful to look at. Has a nice combination of sweet fruits like mango, sweet grapefruit, and sweet oranges. Has a nice blend of malt, and a bit of pine. Has a little bitter finish, but overall a clean finish. Winner!!!

Weird.....

Everyone keeps saying this is really sweet. I did not think this was sweet at all. If anything its like a non sweet cream soda. That is it... a non sweet cream soda... nothing else to say.
Has a nice cooper color! Nice smell of malt, and sweet caramel. Nice complex mix of malt, caramel, milk, and bit of hopps. Has a bit of a bitter finish but not overpowering.
Has a light aroma of grapes. Has a light yellow color. Just the worst taste ever. Urinal/spoiled grapefruit juice.... Pass me a miller lite or some dirt to get this awful taste out of my mouth.....
Fairly dark porter. Smells good with roasted nutty flavor. Has a bitter nutty flavor. Not really complex and did not have a pleasant after taste. Maybe will try this again, in case I got a bad one.
Amber color. With a lightly sweet smell, and a touch of pine. It has a light taste. Slightly sweet, a little piney, with a touch of citrus. Overall its a light IPA.
Has a decent cooper color. Has a sweet citrus aroma. Has a light flavor, with some sweetness and malt. Has a dry finish. Its ok....

Not a big coffee fan, but gave it a shot. Smells of roasted coffee. Has a deep opaque color. Has a very strong coffee flavor. Has a mix of milk and sugar. finishes a harsh bitter flavor. It does hide the alcohol fairly well.

Has a deep black pour. Has a rich chocolate aroma. Is a really complex beer. starts off sweet, caramel, chocolate. Then it moves on to biscuits, and huge Belgian yeast. Then it has a citrus, coffee, bitter finish. This keeps your palate guessing.
Pours a light golden color. Has a grassy, floral nose. Has a light lager taste. Slightly sweet, touch of malt, and it does have a clean finish. Not bad but was not my favorite beer.

Has a nice Amber pour. Has a sweet aroma of grapefruit. It has a complex flavor, that starts off a bit sweet. We get a complex grapefruit, bread, floral, and other citrus flavors. It has a solid spicy finish, with a lot of hops. 

 Pours a richer hazey golden amber hue, good haziness, and a frothy offwhite head that dies to a richer ring, laces well overall. Aromas are richer citrus, touches of dough, grapefruit, some bread, and florals. Gentle spice, mellow yeast. Bigger lemon and citrus as it warms. Simple but a hop dominant offering, some gentle dough and a kiss of apple. Initial is medium bodied, offering a firm hopping, bigger touches of dough and fruit, apple, kiss of pear, with grain, dough. Some sweetness invades, touches of yeast, mellow spice. Some dryness. Middle is gentle dough, bread, a kiss of dryness, hops and gentle spice. Backend offers some dryness, gentle earthy dryness, florals, a touch herbal. Mellow sweetness in the middle (as a sort of Imperial Belgian IPA would offer), more dry finish. Gentle spice, dryness. Pretty solid beer with lingering dry citrusy and earthy hops. Florals, some bitterness. Nice lingering head. A well done Imperial Belgian IPA, a kick of malt that preaches lighter more funf ruit presence, rich hop presence, but not a dominant bitter bomb. Tasty, albeit not my style of choice.caramel, bread, hay,

Rich amber color. Has a sweet caramel, raisin, and orange aroma. Starts out sweet, of caramel and raisins. Then moves on to a nutty, biscuits, flavor. It has a nice mix of alcohol, which gives it a bit of a spicy flavor that lingers, but finishes clean.
Pours a golden color. Ha a mild yeast and grapefruit aroma. Has a light flavor of yeast, and grapefruit. It has a dry finish. Not my favorite from this great brewery.

Yellow/orange color. It smells slightly fruity. It starts off with a slightly sweet, fruity, taste. Its not overpowering. It has a thin mouthful. It has a sharp pine with a harsh bitter finish. Good start, bad finish.

Yuck

The aroma is fairly pleasant. It has a beautiful rich black color. The 3 flavors of this beer are smoke (not in a pleasant way), bad coffee, and burnt. I feel like they made some horrible bitter coffee, burnt some extra beans and tossed them in, and then threw a cigarette in the vat.

This beer has an orange color. The aroma is of sweet grapefruit, and orange. This is a complex IPA. It starts out with s sugary, sweet, syrupy, candied fruit. Then you get hit with a huge amount of bitter grapefruit and resin. Then it has a hard spicy finish. I usually do not like beers with a hard after taste, but somehow I really like this one. This one really hides the 11% alcohol.
Dark and hazy pour. Has a sweet and spicy aroma. It had a mix of spiciness, alcohol, and cloves. The cloves really dominate, and left a harsh after taste. Not for me...

Pours a deep golden color. Has a sweet aroma of candied fruit. It has a slightly sweet taste with an overwhelming display of hops. If you are looking for a potent hoppy beer this is the one. Not too bitter, so an easy beer to enjoy
Has a nice amber glow. Smells like fresh baked biscuits. Has a sweet, doughy, malty, mix with a clean finish. Not overly complex, but a pleasure to drink.
lighter in color. It has a pleasant raspberry/blueberry aroma. Not a complex beery, but overall solid. It mixes a sweet caramel, tart raspberry/blueberry flavor. It has a smooth clean finish.

It has a pleasant chocolate aroma. It has a great deep black look. It has a nice mouthful on my palate. I just did not enjoy the flavor of this beer. It does have a sweet brown sugar with milk chocolate taste. However its mixed in with a smoky (cigarette smoke) and earthy (dirt) flavor. It did not mix well. It has a pour finish. Not a beer I am looking to try again.

It has a light golden hue. The aroma is of fresh candied peaches. I love the complex flavor of peaches, apricots, caramel, tons of malt, and rich oak. It has a slightly dry, spicy finishes that leaves a clean palate. I am in the minority on this one, but it was fantastic beer.

Does not have much of an aroma. It has a very pale color. Very generic beer taste. Maybe a hint of pumpkin, but overall not much flavor. Local brewery, so I really wanted to like it. One of the best looking cans on the market.
Pumpkin pie aroma. It pours a rich amber color. It has a nice blend of sweet pumpkin, cinnamon, and nutmeg. Those flavors are blended with a rich malt flavor. Love drinking this when it comes out!

Rich aroma of sweet cherries and milk chocolate. It pours a rich deep black color. It starts of with a nice tart cherry taste, combined with a creamy milk chocolate that is not too sweet. It also has a really nice mouthful. I agree this could be better if it added a nutty flavor, sweet cherry start but sour finish, and a higher alcohol content. However even without this its really really good.

It did not have much of an Aroma. It has a pleasant amber hue. I did not find a "berry" taste to this beer. It has mild grapefruit flavor which is not sweet or bitter just in the middle. It does have a very strong pinenut taste. It has a bitter finishes which lasts. This was one of my least favorites in the pack.
UPDATED: MAY 10, 2014
Aroma of a sweet hoppy, malts. It has a hazy golden color. Lightly sweet, hoppy, malty saison. Overall it has a decent flavor, but a bit lacking. Not bad but did not stand out.
The aroma is of biscuits and caramel. It has a nice amber color. It starts out with a sweet, caramel, toffee, biscuits, and lots of malt. It has a slightly bitter finish. Very rich and flavorful.
